@startuml
actor User

participant "Frontend\n(React / Vite)" as Frontend
participant "Backend\n(FastAPI :8000)" as Backend
participant "Chess.com API" as ChessAPI
participant "Stockfish Service\n(FastAPI :8001)" as StockfishService
database "Database\n(PostgreSQL)" as DB

== Authentication ==

User -> Frontend : Enter credentials
Frontend -> Backend : POST /api/auth/login
Backend -> DB : Verify user credentials
DB --> Backend : User record
Backend --> Frontend : JWT access token
Frontend --> User : Redirect to Dashboard

== Fetch Games ==

User -> Frontend : Submit Chess.com username\n& date range
Frontend -> Backend : GET /api/games?username=&start_date=&end_date=
Backend -> ChessAPI : GET /pub/player/{username}/games/archives
ChessAPI --> Backend : Archive URLs
Backend -> ChessAPI : GET monthly archive URLs
ChessAPI --> Backend : Raw game data (PGN)
Backend -> Backend : Filter & map games by date range
Backend --> Frontend : Game list with PGN
Frontend --> User : Display games table

== Analyse Game ==

User -> Frontend : Select game to analyse
Frontend -> Backend : POST /api/analysis/start\n{ user_id, game_id, pgn, depth }
Backend --> Frontend : HTTP 202 Accepted
Backend -> StockfishService : POST /analyze\n{ game_id, pgn, depth }

loop For each move
    StockfishService -> StockfishService : Evaluate position (FEN)
end

StockfishService --> Backend : AnalysisResponse\n(per-move evaluations)
Backend -> DB : Save game_history record
Backend -> DB : Save move_analysis records
DB --> Backend : Confirmation

== Poll for Status ==

loop Until status = "done"
    Frontend -> Backend : GET /api/analysis/status/{user_id}/{game_id}
    Backend -> DB : Query move_analysis count
    DB --> Backend : Record count
    Backend --> Frontend : { status: "pending" | "done" }
end

Frontend -> Backend : GET /api/analysis/moves/{game_id}
Backend -> DB : Fetch move_analysis records
DB --> Backend : Move records
Backend --> Frontend : Move-by-move analysis
Frontend --> User : Display board & analysis dashboard

@enduml
